input_text.Prompt: Can you tell me how to stop safari from filling in the address bar on an iphone?
input_text.Response A: Yes, you can disable auto-fill in Safari on your iPhone by going to Settings > Safari > Passwords & AutoFill > AutoFill > Passwords and turning off AutoFill Passwords.
input_text.Response B: Sure, I can help you with that.  Is there a way you can change the settings on your phone so that it doesn’t fill in the address bar?

label_annotations.factors_a: I checked the answer on my iPhone, and the answer given appears to be out-of-date to the current version of iOS.
